definition: to squeeze in/to force oneself into/to cram into/to intrude
to crowd in/to cram in/to force others aside/to press/to squeeze/to find (time in one's busy schedule)
to enter/to go into/to join/to become a member of/to confirm or agree with/abbr. for 入聲|入声[ru4 sheng1]

sentences.english: We stomp the snow into semiflatness and zip into our sleeping bags.
sentences.chinese: 我们把雪地踩成半坡状，并挤入睡袋。

sentences.english: We joined the crowd making for the exit.
sentences.chinese: 我们挤入人群，向出口处涌去。

sentences.english: If pressure is lower, the goal of depth profile control can't be achieved.
sentences.chinese: 如果控制过低，挤入总量往往达不到深度调剖的目的。

sentences.english: As it is squeezed, the gas heats up and radiates X-rays.
sentences.chinese: 随着气体的挤入，气体的温度升高并散发出X射线。

sentences.english: He squeezes himself into a crowded bus every early morning.
sentences.chinese: 每天一大早他都要挤入一班拥挤的公交车。

definition: to break into/to force one's way into/to barge into
to squeeze out/to extrude/to drain/to find the time/to burst out
to crowd in/to cram in/to force others aside/to press/to squeeze/to find (time in one's busy schedule)
to press down/to crush down/to restrain (anger)/to keep down (voice)
